name: Nailed It!
overview: Home bakers who have a poor track record in the kitchen seek redemption -- and cash -- on this series. In each episode, three contestants try their hand at re-creating edible masterpieces. The projects don't always turn out great, but whichever amateur baker comes closest to a successful dessert byÂ the end of the episode takes home the $10,000 prize, which they might want to use on baking lessons. Comic Nicole Byer and renowned pastry chef Jacques Torres host. It's part reality contest, part hot mess.

seasons.name: Double Trouble
seasons.overview: When two clueless cake "artists" team up, the reveals are even more ridiculous. From best buds to brothers and sisters, these bakers are twice as bad.

seasons.name: Halloween
seasons.overview: The Emmy-nominated series is back with a season full of tricks and treats as we celebrate Halloween. Featuring ghoulish surprises from some favorite Netflix shows - The Umbrella Academy, Cobra Kai and The Witcher, the desserts are intentionally scary this time!

episodes.name: First Date to Life Mate
episodes.overview: Under the watchful eyes of an iconic cake designer, contestants decorate complicated cake pops and a bespectacled, three-tiered wedding cake.

episodes.name: Fantasyland
episodes.overview: The bakers do their best to make jelly-filled doughnuts fit for a pirate before tackling an edible tower with a princess on top.

episodes.name: Head Under Water
episodes.overview: Two daunting desserts -- a chocolate-filled "hot tub" and an open-mouthed shark cake -- have the hapless home cooks struggling to stay afloat.

episodes.name: Weird Science
episodes.overview: Contestants loosen up a food scientist with a cupcake-cocktail pairing before serving him questionable slices of a bubbling volcano cake.

episodes.name: Big in Japan
episodes.overview: A YouTube star known for her fondant work watches the bakers try to copy two of her most popular Japanese-themed-cakes.

episodes.name: In Your Face!
episodes.overview: Dogged contestants are seeing double when they're asked to paint their portraits on a cookie before building an edible bust of Donald Trump.

episodes.name: High Society
episodes.overview: The contestants raise the bar with two half-baked "high-society" challenges: late-night munchie-inspired pancakes and a gravity-defying tea cake.

episodes.name: Fictitious and Delicious
episodes.overview: It's "happily ever after" or bust when the bakers try to make fairy tale cupcake pops, then stack cakes in the form of a majestic unicorn.

episodes.name: Tailgate, Failgate
episodes.overview: The cooks divide and conquer to fill sections of a savory snack stadium before building a cake that looks like a barbecue grill.

episodes.name: Holi-daze
episodes.overview: 'Tis the season to be scary when the bakers try their hands at holiday cookies before constructing an elaborate gingerbread house.

episodes.name: Zoo You Bake?
episodes.overview: The contestants face their fears (with very sharp knives) when they carve an animal out of a watermelon and bend cake into the shape of a snake.

episodes.name: Out of This World
episodes.overview: Space-themed challenges throw the hapless bakers for a loop when they're asked to make cosmic cupcakes and a supersized solar system cake.

episodes.name: Bonus: 3, 2, 1... Ya Not Done!
episodes.overview: Five fabulous âNailed Itâ fans visited the test kitchen for a challenge so extra, we had to make it a bonus episode.

episodes.name: Ready to Wear, Ready to Eat
Let's Get Lit
episodes.overview: Two bookish treats inspired by literature set the bakers up for epic fails: Shakespearean stained-glass window cookies and a pop-up "Moby Dick" cake.

episodes.name: The One with the 90's Theme
episodes.overview: Edible ice cream boom boxes made with liquid nitrogen and a fresh and fly fondant-covered cake? Oh, snap â that sounds like a '90s challenge.

episodes.name: Indiana Fails and the Temple of Slop
episodes.overview: Terror awaits the contestamts as they take on two technically demanding desserts: chocolate eggs and alayered sphinx cake, both full of surprises.

episodes.name: Chariots of Failure
episodes.overview: The bakes go for the gold â and miss masterfully â with sports-medal cookies and an elaborate swim cake that's topped with a waffle cone torch.

episodes.name: Jungle Bungle
episodes.overview: Jam-filled animal pastries and a coffecake shaped like a sloth push the contestants out of their comfort zones â and the results are wild.

episodes.name: Howdy, Failure!
episodes.overview: A Western-themed round inspires deep-fried cowboy-duck doughnuts, a root beer-infused rodeo cake...and really bad flavors.

episodes.name: The Big Bake Theory
episodes.overview: From self-frosting bubbling beakers to record-breaking rockets, these science-inspired sweets ask the impossible â and invite kids into the kitchen.

episodes.name: I Do ... Hope I Don't Fail
episodes.overview: The bakers commit to re-creating wedding day desserts, including wedding band mini-cakes and a Vegas-themed masterpiece with moving parts.

episodes.name: We're Gonna Need a Bigger Cake
I've Failed and I Can't Get Up!

5.name: Double Trouble
5.overview: When two clueless cake "artists" team up, the reveals are even more ridiculous. From best buds to brothers and sisters, these bakers are twice as bad.

episodes.name: Im-Paw-sible Cakes
episodes.overview: A funny, furry pet theme finds the cooks concocting giant exotic-animal cookies, then re-creating Nicole's adorable dog, Clyde, in cake form.

episodes.name: Paranormal Pastries
episodes.overview: The bakers make candy apple aliens and a sculpted Loch Ness monster cake based on mysterious creatures from outer space... and the freshwater depths.

episodes.name: C'est Jacques!
episodes.overview: Treats inspired by "Mr. Chocolate" Jacques Torres include lollipop portraits and a cake spiced with cocoa and cayenne. Mais oui laugh? But of course!

episodes.name: History in the Baking
episodes.overview: From cupcakes celebrating famous Black women to a towering Tuskegee Airmen cake, this episode honoring Black history aims high -- and achieves hilarity.

episodes.name: There's a Party in My Mouth!
episodes.overview: Terrible bakers take on a trio of festive holiday-hat mini cakes before tackling a pop-up Groundhog Day cake that's full of surprises.

episodes.name: Everyone Romaine Calm
episodes.overview: A gardening theme gives life to doughy gnomes atop miniature pies and a heathy-ish veggie-patch cake packed with carrots and zucchini.
